Text: Caught wind of a heated debate over whether to keep our pristine beaches or pave them for solar panels.
I suggested a beach-cleanup party, but Brazil just brought more caipirinhas instead.
Trust me, you can’t compost litter if you’re too busy sipping cocktails!
Meanwhile, the US argued about “infrastructure”—like a bridge can beat a sunset.
It’s like trading coconuts for concrete!
If anyone needs a solar charger for their outrage, I’ve got you covered.
